cpqiScsiMibRevMajor.name: cpqiScsiMibRevMajor
cpqiScsiMibRevMajor.description: The Major Revision level. A change in the major revision level represents a major change in the architecture of the MIB. A change in the major revision level may indicate a significant change in the information supported and/or the meaning of the supported information, correct interpretation of data may require a MIB document with the same major revision level.

cpqiScsiMibRevMinor.name: cpqiScsiMibRevMinor
cpqiScsiMibRevMinor.description: The Minor Revision level. A change in the minor revision level may represent some minor additional support; no changes to any pre-existing information has occurred.

cpqiScsiMibCondition.name: cpqiScsiMibCondition
cpqiScsiMibCondition.description: The overall condition. This object represents the overall status of the iSCSI system represented by this MIB.

cpqiScsiInstanceAttributesTable.name: cpqiScsiInstanceAttributesTable
cpqiScsiInstanceAttributesTable.description: A list of iSCSI instances present on the system.

cpqiScsiInstanceAttributesEntry.name: cpqiScsiInstanceAttributesEntry
cpqiScsiInstanceAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiInstIndex
cpqiScsiInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiInstDescr.name: cpqiScsiInstDescr
cpqiScsiInstDescr.description: An octet string, determined by the implementation to describe the iSCSI instance. When only a single instance is present, this object may be set to the zero-length string. with multiple iSCSI instances, it may be used in an implementation-dependent manner to describe the purpose of the respective instance.

cpqiScsiInstVersionMin.name: cpqiScsiInstVersionMin
cpqiScsiInstVersionMin.description: Minimum version number of the iSCSI specification supported by this instance.

cpqiScsiInstVersionMax.name: cpqiScsiInstVersionMax
cpqiScsiInstVersionMax.description: Maximum version number of the iSCSI specification supported by this instance.

cpqiScsiInstVendorID.name: cpqiScsiInstVendorID
cpqiScsiInstVendorID.description: An octet string describing the manufacturer of the implementation of this instance.

cpqiScsiInstVendorVersion.name: cpqiScsiInstVendorVersion
cpqiScsiInstVendorVersion.description: An octet string set by the manufacturer describing the version of the implementation of this instance. The format of this string is determined solely by the manufacturer, and is for informational purposes only. It is unrelated to the iSCSI specification version numbers.

cpqiScsiInstPortalNumber.name: cpqiScsiInstPortalNumber
cpqiScsiInstPortalNumber.description: The number of rows in the cpqiScsiPortalAttributesTable which are currently associated with this iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiInstNodeNumber.name: cpqiScsiInstNodeNumber
cpqiScsiInstNodeNumber.description: The number of rows in the cpqiScsiNodeAttributesTable which are currently associated with this iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiInstSessionNumber.name: cpqiScsiInstSessionNumber
cpqiScsiInstSessionNumber.description: The number of rows in the cpqiScsiSessionAttributesTable which are currently associated with this iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiInstSsnFailures.name: cpqiScsiInstSsnFailures
cpqiScsiInstSsnFailures.description: This object counts the number of times a session belonging to this instance has been failed.

cpqiScsiInstLastSsnFailureType.name: cpqiScsiInstLastSsnFailureType
cpqiScsiInstLastSsnFailureType.description: The counter object in the cpqiScsiInstSsnErrorStatsTable that was incremented when the last session failure occurred. If the reason for failure is not found in the cpqiScsiInstSsnErrorStatsTable, the value { 0.0 } is used instead.

cpqiScsiInstLastSsnRmtNodeName.name: cpqiScsiInstLastSsnRmtNodeName
cpqiScsiInstLastSsnRmtNodeName.description: An octet string describing the name of the remote node from the failed session.

cpqiScsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsTable.name: cpqiScsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsTable
cpqiScsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsTable.description: A list of error types that will cause a session failure.

cpqiScsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsEntry.name: cpqiScsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsEntry
cpqiScsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiInstSsnInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiInstSsnInstIndex
cpqiScsiInstSsnInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiInstSsnDigestErrors.name: cpqiScsiInstSsnDigestErrors
cpqiScsiInstSsnDigestErrors.description: The count of sessions which were failed due to receipt of a PDU containing header or data digest errors.

cpqiScsiInstSsnCxnTimeoutErrors.name: cpqiScsiInstSsnCxnTimeoutErrors
cpqiScsiInstSsnCxnTimeoutErrors.description: The count of sessions which were failed due to a sequence exceeding a time limit.

cpqiScsiInstSsnFormatErrors.name: cpqiScsiInstSsnFormatErrors
cpqiScsiInstSsnFormatErrors.description: The count of sessions which were failed due to receipt of a PDU which contained a format error.

cpqiScsiPortalAttributesTable.name: cpqiScsiPortalAttributesTable
cpqiScsiPortalAttributesTable.description: A list of transport endpoints (using TCP or another transport protocol) used by this iSCSI instance. An iSCSI instance may use a portal to listen for incoming connections to its targets, to initiate connections to other targets, or both.

cpqiScsiPortalAttributesEntry.name: cpqiScsiPortalAttributesEntry
cpqiScsiPortalAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular portal instance.

cpqiScsiPortalInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiPortalInstIndex
cpqiScsiPortalInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiPortalIndex.name: cpqiScsiPortalIndex
cpqiScsiPortalIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular transport endpoint within this iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiPortalRoles.name: cpqiScsiPortalRoles
cpqiScsiPortalRoles.description: A portal can operate in one or both of two roles: as a target portal and/or an initiator portal. If the portal will operate in both roles, both bits must be set. When a new cpqiScsiPortalAttributesEntry is to be created, the agent should use this object as a hint for the creation of a new cpqiScsiTgtPortalAttributesEntry and/or cpqiScsiIntrPortalAttributesEntry.

cpqiScsiPortalAddrType.name: cpqiScsiPortalAddrType
cpqiScsiPortalAddrType.description: The type of Internet Network Address in the cpqiScsiPortalAddr.

cpqiScsiPortalProtocol.name: cpqiScsiPortalProtocol
cpqiScsiPortalProtocol.description: The portal's transport protocol. The following values are defined: icmp(1) Internet Control Message igmp(2) Internet Group Management ggp(3) Gateway-to-Gateway ip(4) IP in IP (encapsulation) st(5) Stream tcp(6) Transmission Control

cpqiScsiPortalMaxRecvDataSegLength.name: cpqiScsiPortalMaxRecvDataSegLength
cpqiScsiPortalMaxRecvDataSegLength.description: The maximum PDU length this portal can receive. This may be constrained by hardware characteristics and individual implementations may chose not to allow this object to be changed.

cpqiScsiPortalPrimaryHdrDigest.name: cpqiScsiPortalPrimaryHdrDigest
cpqiScsiPortalPrimaryHdrDigest.description: The preferred header digest for this portal.

cpqiScsiPortalPrimaryDataDigest.name: cpqiScsiPortalPrimaryDataDigest
cpqiScsiPortalPrimaryDataDigest.description: The preferred data digest method for this portal.

cpqiScsiPortalSecondaryHdrDigest.name: cpqiScsiPortalSecondaryHdrDigest
cpqiScsiPortalSecondaryHdrDigest.description: An alternate header digest preference for this portal.

cpqiScsiPortalSecondaryDataDigest.name: cpqiScsiPortalSecondaryDataDigest
cpqiScsiPortalSecondaryDataDigest.description: An alternate data digest preference for this portal.

cpqiScsiPortalRecvMarker.name: cpqiScsiPortalRecvMarker
cpqiScsiPortalRecvMarker.description: This object indicates whether or not this portal will request markers in it's incoming data stream.

cpqiScsiTgtPortalAttributesTable.name: cpqiScsiTgtPortalAttributesTable
cpqiScsiTgtPortalAttributesTable.description: A list of transport endpoints (using TCP or another transport protocol) on which this iSCSI instance listens for incoming connections to its targets.

cpqiScsiTgtPortalAttributesEntry.name: cpqiScsiTgtPortalAttributesEntry
cpqiScsiTgtPortalAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular portal instance that is used to listen for incoming connections to local targets. This row is populated for each cpqiScsiPortalAttributesEntry row that may be used as a target portal.

cpqiScsiTgtPortalInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtPortalInstIndex
cpqiScsiTgtPortalInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiTgtPortalPortalIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtPortalPortalIndex
cpqiScsiTgtPortalPortalIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular transport endpoint within this iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiTgtPortalPort.name: cpqiScsiTgtPortalPort
cpqiScsiTgtPortalPort.description: The portal's transport protocol port number on which the portal listens for incoming iSCSI connections when the portal is used as a target portal.

cpqiScsiTgtPortalTag.name: cpqiScsiTgtPortalTag
cpqiScsiTgtPortalTag.description: The portal's aggregation tag when portal is used as a target portal. Multiple-connection sessions may be aggregated over portals sharing an identical aggregation tag.

cpqiScsiIntrPortalAttributesTable.name: cpqiScsiIntrPortalAttributesTable
cpqiScsiIntrPortalAttributesTable.description: A list of Internet Network Addresses (using TCP or another transport protocol) from which this iSCSI instance may initiate connections to other targets.

cpqiScsiIntrPortalAttributesEntry.name: cpqiScsiIntrPortalAttributesEntry
cpqiScsiIntrPortalAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular portal instance that is used to initiate connections to iSCSI targets. This row is populated for each cpqiScsiPortalAttributesEntry row that may be used as an initiator portal.

cpqiScsiIntrPortalInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiIntrPortalInstIndex
cpqiScsiIntrPortalInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiIntrPortalPortalIndex.name: cpqiScsiIntrPortalPortalIndex
cpqiScsiIntrPortalPortalIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular transport endpoint within this iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiIntrPortalTag.name: cpqiScsiIntrPortalTag
cpqiScsiIntrPortalTag.description: The portal's aggregation tag when the portal is used as an initiator portal. Multiple-connection sessions may be aggregated over portals sharing an identical aggregation tag.

cpqiScsiNodeAttributesTable.name: cpqiScsiNodeAttributesTable
cpqiScsiNodeAttributesTable.description: A list of iSCSI nodes belonging to each iSCSI instance present on the local system. An iSCSI node can act as an initiator, a target, or both.

cpqiScsiNodeAttributesEntry.name: cpqiScsiNodeAttributesEntry
cpqiScsiNodeAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular iSCSI node.

cpqiScsiNodeInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiNodeInstIndex
cpqiScsiNodeInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiNodeNodeIndex.name: cpqiScsiNodeNodeIndex
cpqiScsiNodeNodeIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular node within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiNodeName.name: cpqiScsiNodeName
cpqiScsiNodeName.description: A character string that is a globally unique identifier for this iSCSI node. The node name is independent of the location of the node, and can be resolved into a set of addresses through various discovery services.

cpqiScsiNodeAlias.name: cpqiScsiNodeAlias
cpqiScsiNodeAlias.description: A character string that is a human-readable name or description of the iSCSI node. If configured, this alias may be communicated to the initiator or target node at the remote end of the connection during a Login Request or Response message. This string is not used as an identifier, but can be displayed by the system's user interface in a list of initiators and/or targets to which it is connected. If no alias is configured, this object is a zero-length string.

cpqiScsiNodeRoles.name: cpqiScsiNodeRoles
cpqiScsiNodeRoles.description: A node can operate in one or both of two roles: a target role and/or an initiator role. If the node will operate in both roles, both bits must be set. When a new cpqiScsiNodeAttributesEntry is to be created, the agent should use this object as a hint for the creation of a new cpqiScsiTargetAttributesEntry and/or cpqiScsiInitiatorAttributesEntry.

cpqiScsiNodeTransportType.name: cpqiScsiNodeTransportType
cpqiScsiNodeTransportType.description: A pointer to the corresponding scsiTrnspt object in the SCSI MIB (which in turn points to this iSCSI node) allowing management stations to locate the SCSI-level Device that is represented by this cpqiScsiNode.

cpqiScsiNodeInitialR2T.name: cpqiScsiNodeInitialR2T
cpqiScsiNodeInitialR2T.description: This object indicates the InitialR2T preference for this node: True = YES, False = will try to negotiate NO, will accept YES

cpqiScsiNodeImmediateData.name: cpqiScsiNodeImmediateData
cpqiScsiNodeImmediateData.description: This object indicates ImmediateData preference for this node True = YES (but will accept NO), False = NO

cpqiScsiNodeMaxOutstandingR2T.name: cpqiScsiNodeMaxOutstandingR2T
cpqiScsiNodeMaxOutstandingR2T.description: Maximum number of outstanding R2Ts allowed per task.

cpqiScsiNodeFirstBurstLength.name: cpqiScsiNodeFirstBurstLength
cpqiScsiNodeFirstBurstLength.description: The maximum length (bytes) supported for unsolicited data to/from this node.

cpqiScsiNodeMaxBurstLength.name: cpqiScsiNodeMaxBurstLength
cpqiScsiNodeMaxBurstLength.description: The maximum number of bytes which can be sent within a single sequence of Data-In or Data-Out PDUs.

cpqiScsiNodeMaxConnections.name: cpqiScsiNodeMaxConnections
cpqiScsiNodeMaxConnections.description: The maximum number of connections allowed in each session to and/or from this node.

cpqiScsiNodeDataSequenceInOrder.name: cpqiScsiNodeDataSequenceInOrder
cpqiScsiNodeDataSequenceInOrder.description: The DataSequenceInOrder preference of this node. False (=No) indicates that iSCSI data PDU sequences may be transferred in any order. True (=Yes) indicates that data PDU sequences must be transferred using continuously increasing offsets, except during error recovery.

cpqiScsiNodeDataPDUInOrder.name: cpqiScsiNodeDataPDUInOrder
cpqiScsiNodeDataPDUInOrder.description: The DataPDUInOrder preference of this node. False (=No) indicates that iSCSI data PDUs within sequences may be in any order. True (=Yes) indicates that data PDUs within sequences must be at continuously increasing addresses, with no gaps or overlay between PDUs.

cpqiScsiNodeDefaultTime2Wait.name: cpqiScsiNodeDefaultTime2Wait
cpqiScsiNodeDefaultTime2Wait.description: The DefaultTime2Wait preference of this node. This is the minimum time, in seconds, to wait before attempting an explicit/implicit logout or active task reassignment after an unexpected connection termination or a connection reset.

cpqiScsiNodeDefaultTime2Retain.name: cpqiScsiNodeDefaultTime2Retain
cpqiScsiNodeDefaultTime2Retain.description: The DefaultTime2Retain preference of this node. This is the maximum time, in seconds after an initial wait (Time2Wait), before which an active task reassignment is still possible after an unexpected connection termination or a connection reset.

cpqiScsiNodeErrorRecoveryLevel.name: cpqiScsiNodeErrorRecoveryLevel
cpqiScsiNodeErrorRecoveryLevel.description: The ErrorRecoveryLevel preference of this node. Currently, only 0-2 are valid. This object is designed to accommodate future error recover levels. Higher error recovery levels imply support in addition to support for the lower error level functions. In other words, error level 2 implies support for levels 0-1, since those functions are subsets of error level 2.

cpqiScsiTargetAttributesTable.name: cpqiScsiTargetAttributesTable
cpqiScsiTargetAttributesTable.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular node that can take on a target role.

cpqiScsiTargetAttributesEntry.name: cpqiScsiTargetAttributesEntry
cpqiScsiTargetAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular target.

cpqiScsiTgtInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtInstIndex
cpqiScsiTgtInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiTgtNodeIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtNodeIndex
cpqiScsiTgtNodeIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular node within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiTgtLoginFailures.name: cpqiScsiTgtLoginFailures
cpqiScsiTgtLoginFailures.description: This object counts the number of times a login attempt to this local target has failed.

cpqiScsiTgtLastFailureTime.name: cpqiScsiTgtLastFailureTime
cpqiScsiTgtLastFailureTime.description: The timestamp of the most recent failure of a login attempt to this target. A value of zero indicates that no such failures have occurred.

cpqiScsiTgtLastFailureType.name: cpqiScsiTgtLastFailureType
cpqiScsiTgtLastFailureType.description: The type of the most recent failure of a login attempt to this target, represented as the OID of the counter object in cpqiScsiTargetLoginStatsTable for which the relevant instance was incremented. A value of 0.0 indicates a type which is not represented by any of the counters in cpqiScsiTargetLoginStatsTable.

cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureName.name: cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureName
cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureName.description: An octet string giving the name of the initiator that failed the last login attempt.

cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddrType.name: cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddrType
cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddrType.description: The type of Internet Network Address in cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddr.

cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddr.name: cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddr
cpqiScsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddr.description: An Internet Network Address giving the host address of the initiator that failed the last login attempt.

cpqiScsiTargetLoginStatsTable.name: cpqiScsiTargetLoginStatsTable
cpqiScsiTargetLoginStatsTable.description: A table of counters which keep a record of the results of initiators' login attempts to this target.

cpqiScsiTargetLoginStatsEntry.name: cpqiScsiTargetLoginStatsEntry
cpqiScsiTargetLoginStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing counters for each result of a login attempt to this target.

cpqiScsiTgtLoginInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtLoginInstIndex
cpqiScsiTgtLoginInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiTgtLoginNodeIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtLoginNodeIndex
cpqiScsiTgtLoginNodeIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular node within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiTgtLoginAccepts.name: cpqiScsiTgtLoginAccepts
cpqiScsiTgtLoginAccepts.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status 0x0000, Accept Login, transmitted by this target.

cpqiScsiTgtLoginOtherFails.name: cpqiScsiTgtLoginOtherFails
cpqiScsiTgtLoginOtherFails.description: The number of Login Response PDUs which were transmitted by this target, and which were not counted by any other object in the row.

cpqiScsiTgtLoginRedirects.name: cpqiScsiTgtLoginRedirects
cpqiScsiTgtLoginRedirects.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status class 0x01, Redirection, transmitted by this target.

cpqiScsiTgtLoginAuthorizeFails.name: cpqiScsiTgtLoginAuthorizeFails
cpqiScsiTgtLoginAuthorizeFails.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status 0x0202, Forbidden Target, transmitted by this target. If this counter is incremented, an cpqiScsiTgtLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cpqiScsiTgtLoginAuthenticateFails.name: cpqiScsiTgtLoginAuthenticateFails
cpqiScsiTgtLoginAuthenticateFails.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status 0x0201, Authentication Failed, transmitted by this target If this counter is incremented, an cpqiScsiTgtLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cpqiScsiTgtLoginNegotiateFails.name: cpqiScsiTgtLoginNegotiateFails
cpqiScsiTgtLoginNegotiateFails.description: The number of times a target has effectively refused a login because the parameter negotiation failed. [Ed. While this situation can occur, the exact mechanism is as yet undefined in the iSCSI Protocol Spec.] If this counter is incremented, an cpqiScsiTgtLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cpqiScsiTargetLogoutStatsTable.name: cpqiScsiTargetLogoutStatsTable
cpqiScsiTargetLogoutStatsTable.description: When a target receives a Logout command, it responds with a Logout Response that carries a status code. This table contains counters for both normal and abnormal logout requests received by this target.

cpqiScsiTargetLogoutStatsEntry.name: cpqiScsiTargetLogoutStatsEntry
cpqiScsiTargetLogoutStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing counters of Logout Response PDUs that were received by this target.

cpqiScsiTgtLogoutInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtLogoutInstIndex
cpqiScsiTgtLogoutInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiTgtLogoutNodeIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtLogoutNodeIndex
cpqiScsiTgtLogoutNodeIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular node within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiTgtLogoutNormals.name: cpqiScsiTgtLogoutNormals
cpqiScsiTgtLogoutNormals.description: The count of Logout Command PDUs received by this target, with reason code 0 (closes the session).

cpqiScsiTgtLogoutOthers.name: cpqiScsiTgtLogoutOthers
cpqiScsiTgtLogoutOthers.description: The count of Logout Command PDUs received by this target, with any status code other than 0.

cpqiScsiTgtAuthAttributesTable.name: cpqiScsiTgtAuthAttributesTable
cpqiScsiTgtAuthAttributesTable.description: A list of initiator identities that are authorized to access each target node within each iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiTgtAuthAttributesEntry.name: cpqiScsiTgtAuthAttributesEntry
cpqiScsiTgtAuthAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular target node's authorized initiator identity.

cpqiScsiTgtAuthInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtAuthInstIndex
cpqiScsiTgtAuthInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiTgtAuthNodeIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtAuthNodeIndex
cpqiScsiTgtAuthNodeIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular node within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiTgtAuthIndex.name: cpqiScsiTgtAuthIndex
cpqiScsiTgtAuthIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular target's authorized initiator identity within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiTgtAuthIdentity.name: cpqiScsiTgtAuthIdentity
cpqiScsiTgtAuthIdentity.description: A pointer to the corresponding IPS-AUTH MIB user entry that will be allowed to access this iSCSI target.

cpqiScsiInitiatorAttributesTable.name: cpqiScsiInitiatorAttributesTable
cpqiScsiInitiatorAttributesTable.description: A list of iSCSI nodes that can take on an initiator role, belonging to each iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiInitiatorAttributesEntry.name: cpqiScsiInitiatorAttributesEntry
cpqiScsiInitiatorAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular iSCSI node that has initiator capabilities.

cpqiScsiIntrInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiIntrInstIndex
cpqiScsiIntrInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiIntrNodeIndex.name: cpqiScsiIntrNodeIndex
cpqiScsiIntrNodeIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular node within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiIntrLoginFailures.name: cpqiScsiIntrLoginFailures
cpqiScsiIntrLoginFailures.description: This object counts the number of times a login attempt from this local initiator has failed.

cpqiScsiIntrLastFailureTime.name: cpqiScsiIntrLastFailureTime
cpqiScsiIntrLastFailureTime.description: The timestamp of the most recent failure of a login attempt from this initiator. A value of zero indicates that no such failures have occurred.

cpqiScsiIntrLastFailureType.name: cpqiScsiIntrLastFailureType
cpqiScsiIntrLastFailureType.description: The type of the most recent failure of a login attempt from this initiator, represented as the OID of the counter object in cpqiScsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable for which the relevant instance was incremented. A value of 0.0 indicates a type which is not represented by any of the counters in cpqiScsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable.

cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureName.name: cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureName
cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureName.description: An octet string giving the name of the target that failed the last login attempt.

cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddrType.name: cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddrType
cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddrType.description: The type of Internet Network Address in cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddr.

cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddr.name: cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddr
cpqiScsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddr.description: An Internet Network Address giving the host address of the target that failed the last login attempt.

cpqiScsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable.name: cpqiScsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable
cpqiScsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable.description: A table of counters which keep track of the results of this initiator's login attempts.

cpqiScsiInitiatorLoginStatsEntry.name: cpqiScsiInitiatorLoginStatsEntry
cpqiScsiInitiatorLoginStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing counters of each result of this initiator's login attempts.

cpqiScsiIntrLoginInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiIntrLoginInstIndex
cpqiScsiIntrLoginInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiIntrLoginNodeIndex.name: cpqiScsiIntrLoginNodeIndex
cpqiScsiIntrLoginNodeIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular node within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiIntrLoginAcceptRsps.name: cpqiScsiIntrLoginAcceptRsps
cpqiScsiIntrLoginAcceptRsps.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status 0x0000, Accept Login, received by this initiator.

cpqiScsiIntrLoginOtherFailRsps.name: cpqiScsiIntrLoginOtherFailRsps
cpqiScsiIntrLoginOtherFailRsps.description: The count of Login Response PDUs received by this initiator with any status code not counted in the objects below.

cpqiScsiIntrLoginRedirectRsps.name: cpqiScsiIntrLoginRedirectRsps
cpqiScsiIntrLoginRedirectRsps.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status class 0x01, Redirection, received by this initiator.

cpqiScsiIntrLoginAuthFailRsps.name: cpqiScsiIntrLoginAuthFailRsps
cpqiScsiIntrLoginAuthFailRsps.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status class 0x201, Authentication Failed, received by this initiator.

cpqiScsiIntrLoginAuthenticateFails.name: cpqiScsiIntrLoginAuthenticateFails
cpqiScsiIntrLoginAuthenticateFails.description: The number of times the initiator has aborted a login because the target could not be authenticated. No response is generated. If this counter is incremented, an cpqiScsiIntrLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cpqiScsiIntrLoginNegotiateFails.name: cpqiScsiIntrLoginNegotiateFails
cpqiScsiIntrLoginNegotiateFails.description: The number of times the initiator has aborted a login because parameter negotiation with the target failed. No response is generated. If this counter is incremented, an cpqiScsiIntrLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cpqiScsiInitiatorLogoutStatsTable.name: cpqiScsiInitiatorLogoutStatsTable
cpqiScsiInitiatorLogoutStatsTable.description: When an initiator attempts send a Logout command, the target responds with a Logout Response that carries a status code. This table contains a list of counters of Logout Response PDUs of each status code, that were received by each initiator belonging to this iSCSI instance present on this system.

cpqiScsiInitiatorLogoutStatsEntry.name: cpqiScsiInitiatorLogoutStatsEntry
cpqiScsiInitiatorLogoutStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing counters of Logout Response PDUs of each status code, that were generated by this initiator.

cpqiScsiIntrLogoutInstIndex.name: cpqiScsiIntrLogoutInstIndex
cpqiScsiIntrLogoutInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular iSCSI instance.

cpqiScsiIntrLogoutNodeIndex.name: cpqiScsiIntrLogoutNodeIndex
cpqiScsiIntrLogoutNodeIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular node within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cpqiScsiIntrLogoutNormals.name: cpqiScsiIntrLogoutNormals
cpqiScsiIntrLogoutNormals.description: The count of Logout Command PDUs generated by this initiator with reason code 0 (closes the session).

cpqiScsiIntrLogoutOthers.name: cpqiScsiIntrLogoutOthers
cpqiScsiIntrLogoutOthers.description: The count of Logout Command PDUs generated by this initiator with any status code other than 0.

cpqiScsiIntrAuthAttributesTable.name: cpqiScsiIntrAuthAttributesTable
cpqiScsiIntrAuthAttributesTable.description: A list of target identities which each initiator on the local system may access.

cpqiScsiIntrAuthAttributesEntry.name: cpqiScsiIntrAuthAttributesEntry
cpqiScsiIntrAuthAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular initiator node's authorized target identity.

cpqiScsiSsnDirection.name: cpqiScsiSsnDirection
cpqiScsiSsnDirection.description: Direction of iSCSI session: InboundSession - session is established from an external initiator to a target within this iSCSI instance. OutboundSession - session is established from an initiator within this iSCSI instance to an external target.

cpqiScsiSsnInitiatorName.name: cpqiScsiSsnInitiatorName
cpqiScsiSsnInitiatorName.description: If cpqiScsiSsnDirection is Inbound, this object is an octet string that will contain the name of the remote initiator. If this session is a discovery session that does not specify a particular initiator, this object will contain a zero-length string. If cpqiScsiSsnDirection is Outbound, this object will contain a zero-length string.

cpqiScsiSsnTargetName.name: cpqiScsiSsnTargetName
cpqiScsiSsnTargetName.description: If cpqiScsiSsnDirection is Outbound, this object is an octet string that will contain the name of the remote target. If this session is a discovery session that does not specify a particular target, this object will contain a zero-length string. If cpqiScsiSsnDirection is Inbound, this object will contain a zero-length string.

cpqiScsiSsnTSIH.name: cpqiScsiSsnTSIH
cpqiScsiSsnTSIH.description: The target-defined identification handle for this session.

cpqiScsiSsnISID.name: cpqiScsiSsnISID
cpqiScsiSsnISID.description: The initiator-defined portion of the iSCSI Session ID.

cpqiScsiSsnInitiatorAlias.name: cpqiScsiSsnInitiatorAlias
cpqiScsiSsnInitiatorAlias.description: An octet string that gives the alias communicated by the initiator end of the session during the login phase. If no alias exists, the value is a zero-length string.

cpqiScsiSsnTargetAlias.name: cpqiScsiSsnTargetAlias
cpqiScsiSsnTargetAlias.description: An octet string that gives the alias communicated by the target end of the session during the login phase. If no alias exists, the value is a zero-length string.

cpqiScsiSsnInitialR2T.name: cpqiScsiSsnInitialR2T
cpqiScsiSsnInitialR2T.description: If set to true, indicates that the initiator must wait for an R2T before sending to the target. If set to false, the initiator may send data immediately, within limits set by cpqiScsiSsnFirstBurstLength and the expected data transfer length of the request. Default is true.

cpqiScsiSsnImmediateData.name: cpqiScsiSsnImmediateData
cpqiScsiSsnImmediateData.description: Indicates whether the initiator and target have agreed to support immediate data on this session.

cpqiScsiSsnType.name: cpqiScsiSsnType
cpqiScsiSsnType.description: Type of iSCSI session: normalSession - session is a normal iSCSI session discoverySession - session is being used only for discovery.

cpqiScsiSsnMaxOutstandingR2T.name: cpqiScsiSsnMaxOutstandingR2T
cpqiScsiSsnMaxOutstandingR2T.description: The maximum number of outstanding request-to-transmit (R2T)s per task within this session.

cpqiScsiSsnFirstBurstLength.name: cpqiScsiSsnFirstBurstLength
cpqiScsiSsnFirstBurstLength.description: The maximum length supported for unsolicited data sent within this session.

cpqiScsiSsnMaxBurstLength.name: cpqiScsiSsnMaxBurstLength

cpqiScsiSsnConnectionNumber.name: cpqiScsiSsnConnectionNumber

cpqiScsiSsnAuthIdentity.name: cpqiScsiSsnAuthIdentity
cpqiScsiSsnAuthIdentity.description: This object contains a row in the IPS-AUTH MIB which identifies the authentication method being used on this session, as communicated during the login phase.

cpqiScsiSsnDataSequenceInOrder.name: cpqiScsiSsnDataSequenceInOrder
cpqiScsiSsnDataSequenceInOrder.description: False indicates that iSCSI data PDU sequences may be transferred in any order. True indicates that data PDU sequences must be transferred using continuously increasing offsets, except during error recovery.

cpqiScsiSsnDataPDUInOrder.name: cpqiScsiSsnDataPDUInOrder
cpqiScsiSsnDataPDUInOrder.description: False indicates that iSCSI data PDUs within sequences may be in any order. True indicates that data PDUs within sequences must be at continuously increasing addresses, with no gaps or overlay between PDUs. Default is true.

cpqiScsiSsnErrorRecoveryLevel.name: cpqiScsiSsnErrorRecoveryLevel
cpqiScsiSsnErrorRecoveryLevel.description: The level of error recovery negotiated between the initiator and the target. Higher numbers represent more detailed recovery schemes.

The actual count of data octets equals the cpqiScsiSsnTxDataOctets times 2^32 plus the cpqiScsiSsnLCTxDataOctets.

cpqiScsiSsnRxDataOctets.name: cpqiScsiSsnRxDataOctets
